title: Print, "A park of a castle", ca. 1650
markings: Watermark: coat of arms with three five-pointed stars, in chief, three, 2–1 [see accession ledger for illustration]
creditline: Museum purchase through gift of Mrs. John Innes Kane
description: Angle view of a park terrace with a casino, center. Two workment work on the bottom road before a garden pasture, right foreground. Two riders are near them. Address, bottom right: van Merlen Avec Priulege
